00:01:34.420 --> 00:01:36.160
even if they have
no basis in reality.

00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:39.220
Because if we tell it
to ourselves enough

00:01:39.220 --> 00:01:40.710
we eventually start
to believe it.

00:01:40.710 --> 00:01:42.251
And there's a
psychological principle

00:01:42.251 --> 00:01:44.450
called confirmation
bias that confirms this.

00:01:44.450 --> 00:01:47.620
Confirmation bias that
confirms this, that's funny.

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:49.380
What confirmation
bias essentially does

00:01:49.380 --> 00:01:51.210
is it says that you
filter out things

00:01:51.210 --> 00:01:53.370
that don't conform to
what you already believe.

00:01:53.370 --> 00:01:55.910
And you willfully
seek out things

00:01:55.910 --> 00:01:57.930
that will conform to
what you already believe.

00:01:57.930 --> 00:02:00.260
It will confirm your beliefs.

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:02.520
So, you probably
have realized this.

00:02:02.520 --> 00:02:04.480
If you've ever been
car shopping you

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:07.440
