00:51:10.040 --> 00:51:13.310
So I think, one
specific story, no.

00:51:13.310 --> 00:51:15.120
But I think the reason
people gravitate

00:51:15.120 --> 00:51:17.740
towards certain fields
sometimes is just that.

00:51:17.740 --> 00:51:20.490
They feel like they have this
desire to express themselves

00:51:20.490 --> 00:51:23.250
and they find
sanctuary somewhere.

00:51:23.250 --> 00:51:27.460
As a story on a personal note
that sort of resonates with me.

00:51:27.460 --> 00:51:28.870
I have two siblings.

00:51:28.870 --> 00:51:29.812
One is a musician.

00:51:29.812 --> 00:51:31.020
The other's in music theater.

00:51:31.020 --> 00:51:31.930
And I'm a writer.

00:51:31.930 --> 00:51:34.530
And all three of us were sort
of attracted to that early on.

00:51:34.530 --> 00:51:37.550
All three of us did terribly
in the school systems

00:51:37.550 --> 00:51:39.452
until we arrived at
that place of study

00:51:39.452 --> 00:51:41.410
where we could actually
do what we wanted to do

00:51:41.410 --> 00:51:43.070
and then thrived.

00:51:43.070 --> 00:51:45.567
So it happens.

00:51:45.567 --> 00:51:46.650
AUDIENCE: The talk it out.

